<h2>Computational notes</h2>

<p>MedCalc uses the "N-1" Chi-squared test as recommended by Campbell (2007=
) and Richardson (2011).</p>
<p>The confidence interval is calculated according to the recommended metho=
d given by Altman et al. (2000).</p>

<h2>Literature</h2>

<ul>
<li>Altman DG, Machin D, Bryant TN, Gardner MJ (Eds) (2000) Statistics with=
 confidence, 2<sup>nd</sup> ed. BMJ Books. (p. 49) =20
</li><li>Campbell I (2007) Chi-squared and Fisher-Irwin tests of two-by-two=
 tables with small sample recommendations. Statistics in Medicine 26:3661-3=
675.  <a class=3D"undecorated" href=3D"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1=
7315184"><img src=3D"https://www.medcalc.org/common/svg/pubmed.svg" alt=3D"=
